			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				To the previous poster who said this bear was not easy, you aren't doing it right if its not easy for you, especially if you have a pet.  I doubt I could have solely meleed it myself, but at 29 I took the bear out.  All you need to do is plaster it with DOTs, roughly 5 or 6 of them and just play around with it until it dies.  The reason your Winters Roar didn't work on it is because it is 100% resistant to our shamanic DD's, the cold ones at any rate.  As a side note, I saw one ingot drop in 30+ hours, which does make me glad I'm not doing the cleric armor quests.
				</font>
			</td>

